   250                                  ; Actually generate the maze
   251                                  ; maze_generate carves a unique path through the maze from any point to any other point.
   252                                  ;
   253                                  ; helper functions:
   254                                  ; maze_traverse starts at the traverse points and carves a random path
   255                                  ; through the maze until it reaches a dead end, indicated by there
   256                                  ; being no unvisited neighbors, which is when it returns to the caller.
   257                                  ;
   258                                  ; maze_get_unvis_ptr takes the index of the unvis_neighs array and returns a pointer
   259                                  ; in RSI to the actual data (offset_h and offset_w pair).
